{"phase":"planning","outcome":{"note":{}},"id":"30-234","ticketId":"30","at":805831722.156847,"detail":"thinking: Here is my concrete report of the facts:\n\n---\n\n## Investigation Report: Issue #30 — GradeNA + Unsupported\n\n### 1. Project identity\n\n- **Module**: `github.com\/iksnae\/code-certification` (Go 1.25.5)\n- **Domain types package**: `internal\/domain\/` — zero external deps, shared vocabulary\n- **Verification**: `go test .\/... -count=1`\n\n### 2. Target file 1: `internal\/domain\/dimension.go`\n\n**Grade type** (lines 104–113): `type Grade int` with `iota` constants (GradeA=0, GradeAMinus=1, … GradeF=6).\n\n```go\ntype Grade int\n\nconst (\n    GradeA      Grade = iota \/\/ 0.93+\n    GradeAMinus              \/\/ 0.90+\n    GradeBPlus               \/\/ 0.87+\n    GradeB                   \/\/ 0.80+\n    GradeC                   \/\/ 0.70+\n    GradeD                   \/\/ 0.60+\n    GradeF                   \/\/ < 0.60\n)\n```\n\n**gradeStrings map** (lines 116–125): maps each Grade to its letter string; used by `Grade.String()`.\n\n**GradeFromScore** (lines 135–151): float thresholds → Grade; returns GradeF as fallback. Never returns an \"N\/A\" concept.\n\n**Critical type constraint**: The issue's instruction `GradeNA Grade = \"N\/A\"` is **pseudocode** — `Grade` has `int` underlying type; you cannot assign a string literal. The viable Go implementation is a **numeric sentinel outside the iota block** so existing constants' values are undisturbed:\n\n```go\n\/\/ GradeNA is the sentinel grade for unsupported languages.\nconst GradeNA Grade = -1\n```\n\nThis respects all non-goals: does not alter existing grade constants, does not change `GradeFromScore` logic. Then add `GradeNA: \"N\/A\"` to the `gradeStrings` map so `GradeNA.String()` returns `\"N\/A\"`.\n\n### 3. Target file 2: `internal\/domain\/record.go`\n\n**CertificationRecord struct** (lines 86–115): the trust record for a code unit. Add the `Unsupported bool` field — purely additive, zero-value `false` preserves all existing behavior. The field doesn't exist in `recordJSON` (store.go:19–34), so it will be silently dropped on serialization and default to `false` on deserialization — no breakage.\n\n### 4. Downstream aware — NOT in scope but worth noting\n\n**`parseGrade` in `internal\/record\/store.go:515-524`**: hardcodes mappings for A–F only; missing \"N\/A\" → would fallback to `GradeF`. The `store.go` is not a target file for this issue, so this gap persists. When `GradeNA` is stored via `toJSON` (which calls `g.String()` → \"N\/A\"), re-reading via `fromJSON` → `parseGrade(\"N\/A\")` returns `GradeF`. This is a **known round-trip gap** for a follow-up (likely the parent issue #25 or another split).\n\n**`language_tiers` package**: does not exist yet — part of parent issue #25.\n\n### 5. Existing tests\n\n- **`dimension_test.go`**: Tests `TestGrade_String` (A through F only) and `TestDimensionScores_Grade` (GradeFromScore thresholds). No test for a GradeNA sentinel or \"N\/A\" string.\n- **`record_test.go`**: Tests Status, ParseStatus, IsPassing, GenerateRunID, CertificationRun fields. No test for `Unsupported` field.\n- Both will need new test cases for the additions.\n\n### 6. Concrete changes\n\n| File | Change | Detail |\n|------|--------|--------|\n| `internal\/domain\/dimension.go` | Add `const GradeNA Grade = -1` | New const block before\/after the existing iota block (not inside it) |\n| `internal\/domain\/dimension.go` | Add `GradeNA: \"N\/A\"` to `gradeStrings` | So `GradeNA.String()` → `\"N\/A\"` |\n| `internal\/domain\/record.go` | Add `Unsupported bool \\`json:\"unsupported,omitempty\"\\`` to `CertificationRecord` | Purely additive; zero-value false preserves existing behaviour |\n\nBoth are zero-risk, purely additive, and pass the non-goal constraints."}
